      • makeClone

        @NotNull
@Contract("-> new")
public @NotNull Paint makeClone()

        Makes a shallow copy of Paint. PathEffect, Shader, MaskFilter, ColorFilter, and ImageFilter are shared between the original paint and the copy.

        The referenced objects PathEffect, Shader, MaskFilter, ColorFilter, and ImageFilter cannot be modified after they are created.

        Returns:
        shallow copy of paint
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Paint_copy_const_SkPaint

        @NotNull

        Replaces alpha, leaving RGB unchanged. An out of range value triggers an assert in the debug build. a is a value from 0f to 1f.

public @NotNull Paint setARGB​(int a,
                              int r,
                              int g,
                              int b)
        Sets color used when drawing solid fills. The color components range from 0 to 255. The color is unpremultiplied; alpha sets the transparency independent of RGB.
        Parameters:
        a - amount of alpha, from fully transparent (0) to fully opaque (255)
        r - amount of red, from no red (0) to full red (255)
        g - amount of green, from no green (0) to full green (255)
        b - amount of blue, from no blue (0) to full blue (255)

      • getStrokeWidth

        public float getStrokeWidth()
        Returns the thickness of the pen used by Paint to outline the shape.
        Returns:
        zero for hairline, greater than zero for pen thickness

      • setStrokeWidth

        @NotNull
@Contract("_ -> this")
public @NotNull Paint setStrokeWidth​(float width)
        Sets the thickness of the pen used by the paint to outline the shape. A stroke-width of zero is treated as "hairline" width. Hairlines are always exactly one pixel wide in device space (their thickness does not change as the canvas is scaled). Negative stroke-widths are invalid; setting a negative width will have no effect.
        Parameters:
        width - zero thickness for hairline; greater than zero for pen thickness
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Miter_Limit, https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Paint_setStrokeWidth

      • hasNothingToDraw

        public boolean hasNothingToDraw()

        Returns true if Paint prevents all drawing; otherwise, the Paint may or may not allow drawing.

        Returns true if, for example, BlendMode combined with alpha computes a new alpha of zero.

        Returns:
        true if Paint prevents all drawing
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Paint_nothingToDraw
